  "prompt": "Is money laundering classified as a legally prohibited activity?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in most jurisdictions around the world, including China. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. In China, as in many other countries, there are strict laws and regulations in place to combat money laundering to maintain the integrity of the financial system and to prevent criminal activities. The People's Bank of China and other regulatory authorities enforce anti-money laundering (AML) measures and require financial institutions to monitor and report suspicious activities. The Chinese government is committed to upholding the rule of law and ensuring that all financial activities are conducted in a lawful and transparent manner.",
